systemc (2.3.0) stable; urgency=low
  * Compliance to IEEE Std 1666-2011
  * Per LRM, includes TLM-2.0.2
  * Bug fixes.
  * Code cleanup.

 -- Andy Goodrich <acg@forteds.com>  Sun, 01 Jul 2012 00:00:00 -0000

systemc (2.2) stable; urgency=low
  * Compliance to IEEE Std 1666-2005
  * Bug fixes.
  * Code cleanup.
  * Major new functionality
   - Compliance with the IEEE 1666 SystemC Language reference module.
  * Platforms and compilers supported (added since 2.1):
   - Support for 64-bit Linux systems gcc-3.4.3.
   - Linux with GNU C++ compiler version gcc-4.0.1.
   - MacOS X with GNU C++ compiler version gcc-4.0.0.

 -- Andy Goodrich <acg@forteds.com>  Wed, 14 Mar 2007 00:00:00 -0000

systemc (2.1) stable; urgency=low
  * Bug fixes.
  * Code cleanup.
  * Major new functionality
   - Dynamic process support, including synchronization primitives.
   - Mixed concatenation and concatenation of long types.
   - Event queue support.
   - Exported interfaces: sc_export.
   - New error reporting API.
  * Platforms and compilers supported (added since 2.0.1 Production):
   - Solaris 2.8 with Sun CC compiler version Forte 7 and gcc-3.2.3
   - Linux (Redhat 9.0) with GNU C++ compiler version gcc-3.2.2
   - Linux (Redhat 8.0) with GNU C++ compiler version gcc-2.95.3 and gcc-3.2.3
   - MacOS X with GNU C++ compiler version gcc-3.1 and gcc-3.3.
   - Windows NT 4.0 (SP6a) with VC++ 7.0

 -- Andy Goodrich <acg@forteds.com>  Thu, 14 Jul 2005 00:00:00 -0000

systemc (2.0.1) stable; urgency=low
  * Bug fixes.
  * Code cleanup.
  * Simple bus example included.
  * Platforms supported (changed from 2.0 Production):
   - Sun Solaris 2.7 and 2.8 with GNU C++ compiler version gcc-2.95.3
   - Linux (Redhat 6.2) with GNU C++ compiler version gcc-2.95.3
   - Linux (Redhat 7.2) with GNU C++ compiler version gcc-2.95.3
   - HP-UX 11.00 with HP C++ compiler version A.03.33
       (Note: +O1 is the highest safe optimization level)
   - Windows NT 4.0 (SP6a) with VC++ 6.0 (SP5)
  * First release of a regression test suite for SystemC.
     The SystemC regression test suite is released separately.

 -- Martin Janssen  <mjanssen@synopsys.com>  Fri, 05 Apr 2002 00:00:00 -0000

systemc (2.0) stable; urgency=low
  * All new SystemC 2.0 core language features.
  * All SystemC 1.0.2 functionality (except obsoleted SystemC 0.9 features).
  * No methodology-specific channels as in SystemC 1.2.1 beta.
     (Note: starting with this release, the 2.0 Core Language Features
      will be released separately from the methodology-specific libraries,
      an example of which is the Master-Slave Library of 1.2.1 beta.
      The release of the Master-Slave Library will follow this release.
      You would be able to use the Master-Slave Library in conjunction with
      this release).
  * Dynamic thread creation example provided.
  * Directory structure changed from 1.0.2, but same as 2.0 beta-2.
  * Build process changed from 1.0.2 but same as 2.0 beta-2.
  * Bug fixes for 2.0 beta-2.
  * Platforms supported (changed from 2.0 beta-2):
   - Sun Solaris 2.7 and 2.8 with GNU C++ compiler version 2.95.2
   - Sun Solaris 2.7 and 2.8 with SC6.1 and SC6.2
   - Linux (Redhat 6.2) with GNU C++ compiler version 2.95.2
   - HP-UX 11.00 with aCC C++ compiler versions A.03.31 and A.03.15
       (Note: +O1 is the highest safe optimization level)
   - Windows NT 4.0 (SP3 and higher) with VC++6.0

 -- Martin Janssen  <mjanssen@synopsys.com>  Fri, 05 Oct 2001 00:00:00 -0000
